The paper discusses the development of a machine learning algorithm for detecting Ventricular Fibrillation from ECG signals. The algorithm uses a combination of signal processing techniques and a Support Vector Machine for classification. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.BE (Biological Physics), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.SI (Signal Processing), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
